<subSubSection pageId="274" pageNumber="275" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="274" pageNumber="275">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="274" pageNumber="275">
Worldwide, with about 495 species (Lorenz 2005: 135-141 and the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1842" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Scaraphites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="274" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="274" pageNumber="275">Scaraphites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Westwood) placed in 42 genera arrayed in four subtribes: 
<taxonomicName genus="Acanthoscelitina" lsidName="" pageId="274" pageNumber="275" rank="genus">Acanthoscelitina</taxonomicName>
(one species on the southwest coast of Africa), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Andrewes" authorityYear="1929" genus="Oxylobina" lsidName="" pageId="274" pageNumber="275" rank="genus">Oxylobina</taxonomicName>
(29 Asian species in the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Oxylobus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="274" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="274" pageNumber="275">Oxylobus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Putzeys" authorityYear="1867" genus="Scapterina" lsidName="" pageId="274" pageNumber="275" rank="genus">Scapterina</taxonomicName>
(22 species in the Eastern Hemisphere except Europe), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" genus="Scaritina" lsidName="" pageId="274" pageNumber="275" rank="genus">Scaritina</taxonomicName>
(about 445 species).
</paragraph>
